    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Study of the Performance Management Process at Pepsico and Deriving a Relationship between Performance Management, Employee Motivation and Performance on Strategic Objectives of Organization</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Rupam Gogoi</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Performance Management<br />Performance on Strategic</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5955</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The study undertaken with reference to the internship period involves a study of and an on the job role in the functionalities of the Human Resource Department at Pepsico India Holdings Pvt. Ltd. The internship period undergone involved working on live projects as part of the Human Resources team for South Market Unit of Pepsico. As part of the internship duties ongoing projects were executed. This report thereby seeks to encapsulate the learning derived from the internship period. The projects executed were mainly in the areas of Performance Management, Training and Development,work life balance management etc. This report constructs the experience derived from the Performance Management Process at Pepsico. Performance management process is a structured procedure that seeks to derive a sustained performance by the employee for the organization by sub processes of Appraisal,Objective setting, Review etc. This report is an attempt to therefore draw a relationship structure between the performance management process and employee motivation in the longer operating year which leads them on to either obtain or forego objectives as part of the organization. The conclusive element of this study is to evolve a speculative model which provides a link with performance management and actual performance with motivation derivative as a catalyst.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/11434">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/11434</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9711">MBA-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
